@michael_tigas What was your favorite part?

That’s it! That’s the end of the #WWDC21 keynote. 

I expected a cohesive theme throughout like how widgets overtook the media last year, but I like the changes. 

If anything, Apple was more focused on making all of their devices play nice with each other.
Cool! Object capture can create 3D objects with just photos. Super impressive.

Oh shoot. Safari has tab groups and it changes color to match the website’s color? Aha okayyyyyyyyyy 

I’ve switch from Firefox to Edge, but I think I’m moving to Safari now
New Safari tab design? A surprise, but a welcome one
Shortcuts for Mac? Niiiiiiiiiiice
Continuity looks good as always. Not bad, not bad
What are the devices Apple is using for the Home set? My Ring’s camera does not look that HD lol
Omg the TV feature “For All of You” is exactly what I need across streaming services. Everyone has different tastes and needs, finding something to watch seems like a side-hustle
Next is HomeKit but I just want to say that the stage sets are well-designed
Mmm WatchOS feels underwhelming. I mean tbh, it’s already a great wearable. Might have to wait for the next Watch lineup to see any big changes

The Health department at Apple is just on another level. Truly changing lives. 

Detecting your heartbeat accurately, understanding steady walking patterns, lab results with your trends. 

This is why I love analytics so much.

Oh wow, they’ve added a Legacy option for when you pass away, someone you care can access it and make sure your information is dealt properly. 

Also, iCloud+ focuses on privacy features like hiding your email address when you sign-up to websites. No price change! Huh

New privacy summaries is pretty neat. 

As an digital marketing manager, this is scary aha but there’s other ways to find out what people want. It doesn’t have to violate people’s privacyZ
Wait, build apps with Swift in iPad? Okayyyyyyy I’m digging it

I don’t know if the new multitasking feature does it for me. The shelf is useful but doesn’t scream “it feels like a laptop.” 

The quick note features for the iPad feels intuitive. I’m always writing quick notes on my phone.
iPad is next 👀 I hope it can be a laptop/tablet option

My AirPods don’t have a lot of battery life. Would like the Pros since they would fit better in my ears. But I’m glad the accessibility changes Apple is doing. 

I also like that we can find our AirPods much better aha if you lost them, they were pretty much gone

I enjoy Maps and the new design changes. I prefer it over Google’s, but I feel Google’s is more accurate. Without accessing to people’s data, Apple is behind. I don’t mind, because I prefer privacy.

Driving in Downtown Dallas is a nightmare tho lol I hope Apple can focus on it

I don’t know about adding our keys to our phones. Car, home, phone. It’s convenient but I don’t want to depend everything on my phone if it gets stolen.

Also they’re working with adding Driver’s License? Woah

Memories in Photos have nice changes. I use Google Photos to have all my photos on there. The memories highlighted are nice. I do like that Apple can make videos out of photo memories. Don’t know if I should change. 💭

Okay, Intelligent Photos is going to be useful for me. Finally I can get notes on a whiteboard  and have written text sent to my notes. 

This reminds me a bit like Google Lens.
Also, Summary Notifications and Sharing Your Screen might have sherlocked some apps I know.
Notifications! I usually turn off notifications to most applications, they’re just distracting. Glad to see changes. I’m super glad that Do Not Disturb finally turns off everything.
New FaceTime and Message changes has already done it for me. They’ll be super handy for long-distance communication. I hope it can be friendly with 3rd party applications.
